The paper deals with algorithms for data streams and sketching, which are common topics in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The use of randomness and the focus on approximation also suggest that information theory (cs.IT) may be a relevant subfield. The paper also involves computational complexity (cs.CC) in terms of the running time of the algorithm. Additionally, the problem of finding the L1 difference between two vectors is related to topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) such as combinatorics and graph theory. Finally, the use of geometric concepts such as norms and distances suggests that computational geometry (cs.CG) may also be a relevant subfield.
